Existing values are shared by default. Here is what that means in practice.

When you assign one variable to another, both point at the same data:

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    original = "hello"
    copy_of = original
]

No copy happens here. `copy_of` reads the same value as `original`.

### When shared access blocks mutation

A shared alias prevents mutation of the same data while it is still in use.
Once the alias is no longer needed, mutation becomes valid again.

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    items ~= {1, 2, 3}
    view = items
    -- ~items.push(4)  -- would fail: view is still live
    inspect(view)       -- last use of view
    ~items.push(4)      -- valid now
]
